    "ideation": "The file cabinet is an emblem of systematic organization, rhythmic mechanical action, and hidden contents. I'm personifying this by treating the 'eyes' as the labels on a drawer and the 'mouth' as the mechanical sliding rail. The performance begins in a 'locked' state—tight, cold, and rigid. The sequence then depicts a drawer being jerked open (an eye-widening pop), a frantic search through the files (rapid jittering gaze), and the final 'thunk' of the drawer being slammed shut. The color palette transitions from cold steel grays to a brief flash of neon 'data' green as a file is found, before settling back into a dull, professional aluminum gray.",
